  <datafield tag="245" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Correlations in thermal vibrations of crystal atoms. Effect on dechanneling and bremsstrahlung</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="260" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="c">2017-03-24</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">In a crystal, thermal vibrations of neighboring atoms are correlated: long wavelength phonons make them displace in the same direction. These correlations can speed up the dechanneling of axially channeled particles, as shown by a simulation with binary collisions and a Markov chain model of atom vibrations. In the case of <math altimg="si24.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>+</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></math> or <math altimg="si25.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>e</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>-</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></math> at small angle with a crystal axis, the correlated vibrations should give rise to a semi-coherent bremsstrahlung on several consecutive atoms of a row.</subfield>
